  "prompt": "Do VoLTE calls work with data switched off?",
  "response": "No, VoLTE (Voice over LTE) calls typically do not work if mobile data is switched off. VoLTE technology uses the 4G LTE network to transmit voice calls as data packets rather than using the traditional circuit-switched voice networks. Therefore, even though it uses the LTE network, it still requires data services to be enabled, albeit not in the same way as regular internet usage. Disabling mobile data usually affects the ability to make or receive VoLTE calls, as the phone needs to connect to the data network for these calls to be initiated and maintained.",
